HEADWORD: Rainfall
<hw>Rain"fall`</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧n"f⟦add⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
fall or descent of rain; the water, or amount of water, that falls in
rain; <as>as, the average annual <ex>rainfall</ex> of a
region</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Supplied by the <qex>rainfall</qex> of the outer ranges of Sinchul
and Singaleleh.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raininess</ent>⟦br⟧
